Page 4 - 11 : Summary
you want throughput? we got throughput
journey started with poon and dryja in 2015
LN ecosystem can be divided in 6 sectors
technical foundation
implementations: LND, C-Lightning, electrum
routing nodes: acinq
node mgmt: umbrel, greenlight
liquidity: bitrefill
Payments, wallets, savings
wallets: breez, strike(el salvador), bottlepay
merchant payments: breez, btcpay
payment cards, saving in btc, btc economy
finance
lightning native: immature 
dual service: bitfinex, paxful
rewards & earnings
fold, tippin.me
gaming & gambling:
zebedee, satoshi’s games
other 
social apps -imaature
ecomm - immature
3rd layer -immature
 giftcards - bitrefill

Lightning use phases (experimenters & early adopters)
jan - july 2018: baby money, experiments
july 2018 to july 2019: more experiments, more robust, less wild west. 
july 2019: no change in channel capacity: steady experimenting y’all.
jan 21 - present (nov 2021) - early adopters; el salvador legal tender.
wallet payment volume growth far exceeding channel capacity growth
sept 14: the 7M paxful users now lightning integrated
sept 23: 186M twitter users can tip via lightning
akin to reddit onchain tipping in bitcoins early years
Projecting S curves for ridiculous growth
90% of el salvadorians will have access in 4 years time.
Potential followers to el salvador
total 850M people, 650M currently unbanked
have poor banking access
high remittance payment
strong dependance on (fraying) USD

