pg 30-31
intro to the technical founders
LN nodes: 87LND, 11C-L, 2Eclair, 0.1other
pg 32
fig 25 is great: public node percentage reachable per extra hop
1hop (to hub: LNBIG)
2nd hop -> 281nodes. 2% of public nodes
3rd hop - 20-40% public nodes
4th - 70-90% nodes
5th onwards there are poorly connected nodes so it is basically and asymptotic fn
“maintaining and managing your own node is still a technical challenge”
channels can have a tendency to bleed out. options are to
close and re-open a channel
use a liquidity service (thor?)

pg 36.
Bitfinex Fig 26. LN dep& withdrawals were for token sums -- 34%tx.count & 0.45%tx.value 
non-controversial opinion(?): LN is still very much used experimentally for most, if not a subset, of uesers
experimenting with derivative markets in LN-natively is happening (LN Markets)

